title: Why The U.S. Mortgage Market Is Broken
description: For decades, Americans have relied on mortgages to purchase a home. But experts say that several aspects of todayâ€™s mortgage market including cost, the lack of small-dollar loans and lender bias have all greatly hindered Americans from owning their own property. Can the U.S. do anything to fix the broken system and allow mortgages to improve homeownership in America? Watch the video to find out.|Editorâ€™s note and correction (May 27, 2022): A previous version of this video misstated the percentage of nationwide home sales below $100,000 in 2019. The Urban Institute is recalculating its proprietary data after an error was discovered. A similar analysis from the National Association of Realtors shows that the 2019 figure was 8.4%.|High home prices arenâ€™t the only reason behind dwindling homeownership in the U.S. Banks and financial institutions arenâ€™t issuing enough small-dollar mortgages that help families with modest incomes to purchase a property.|â€œIt is particularly hard for people who are buying smaller houses with smaller mortgages to find a lender and to get that mortgage,â€ said Mike Calhoun, president of the Center for Responsible Lending. â€œAnd they also surprisingly are more expensive.â€|And the issue has been getting worse. The value of mortgage loans between $10,000 and $70,000 and between $70,000 and $150,000 dropped by more than 53% and over 21%, respectively, from 2011 to 2021, according to research by Attom Data Solutions. Meanwhile, the value for loans exceeding $150,000 rose by a staggering 240% plus in the same period.|Another study found that denial rates for small-dollar loans were notably higher than denial rates for larger loans. And itâ€™s not because these loans are riskier. Accompanying research found that applicants for small-dollar loans had similar credit profiles to applicants for larger loans.|The real reason is profit.|â€œOne barrier for small-dollar mortgages is that itâ€™s just not as profitable for lenders to do them,â€ according to Janneke Ratcliffe, vice president of the Housing Finance Policy Center at the Urban Institute. â€œLenders get all their fees and interest based on the loan amount so theyâ€™re going to get a lot less revenue on a $70,000 mortgage than they are on a $700,000 mortgage.â€|Â» Subscribe to CNBC: https://cnb.cx/SubscribeCNBC|Â» Subscribe to CNBC TV: https://cnb.cx/SubscribeCNBCtelevision|About CNBC: From 'Wall Street' to 'Main Street' to award winning original documentaries and Reality TV series, CNBC has you covered. title: FIRST DRIVE: Hennessey Venom F5 - Worldâ€™s Maddest Hypercar? 1817bhp 300mph+ Bugatti Rival | Top Gear
description: Say hello to John Hennessy's baby: a love letter to excess horsepower, but not in the form of a tuned truck or muscle car. This is the Hennessey Venom F5, an entirely bespoke extreme-engined hypercar capable of speeds in excess of 300mph. Powering it is an engine appropriately named 'Fury', a whopping 6.6-litre twin-turbo V8 producing 1817bhp. Weighing only 1360kg, the F5 is only 30kg heavier than a Ferrari F8 Tributo but with 1000bhp more. That equals some impressive performance figures: 0-62mph in 2.6s, 0-124mph in 4.7s, and an insane 0-250mph in 15.5s - that's nearly twice as fast as a Bugatti Chiron... description: Kate Moss briefly testified in Johnny Depp's defamation trial against his ex, Amber Heard, on Wednesday. title: Aussie dad devastated from shock DNA testing revealing his kids aren't his | 60 Minutes Australia

Gone is the suspicion, now they're just another weapon in TV's war on crime.  But it might be a different story if that weapon was turned on us.  And that's not impossible.  It's happening to Australian families every day.  DNA testing, especially paternity testing is a booming business - fired up by suspicious husbands determined to prove that the child they're raising is actually theirs.  And as you might imagine, that's opened up a whole new domestic battlefield ... new charges of betrayal and revenge.|WATCH more of 60 Minutes Australia: https://www.60minutes.com.au |LIKE 60 Minutes Australia on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/60Minutes9 |FOLLOW 60 Minutes Australia on Twitter: https://twitter.com/60Mins |FOLLOW 60 Minutes Australia on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/60minutes9|For forty years, 60 Minutes have been telling Australians the worldâ€™s greatest stories. title: Discover Montreal's HIDDEN Supercar Mancave! Visiting the Poirier Collection
description: Welcome to the Poirier Collection! I'm in Montreal, Canada, making my way to Toronto for the Gumball 3000, but first a stop to visit the amazing private garage and ultimate mancave of Luc Poirier. From the Ferrari Big 5 to the latest supercars, let's take a look around!|When I started work on @The Shmuseum, it was exactly this kind of venue that inspired me, and continues to give me ideas and set goals for what I'd like it to become in time. Not only the cars that are part of the collection, but the way it is set up and unique elements that make it different to any other garage.|With Ferrari standing out as the number one brand; the full line up of the Ferrari supercars are featured: LaFerrari Aperta, Enzo, F50, F40 and 288 GTO. The collection continues to also include the full line of the V8 mid-engine supercars including: 488 Pista, 458 Special, 430 Scuderia Spider 16M, 360 Challenge Stradale, F355 Fiorano, 348, 328 and 308, plus the V12s: F12tdf, 599 GTO, 575 SuperAmerica, Testarossa, and more to come.|However, we can also see a Lamborghinin Aventador Ultimae, AMG GT Black Series, Porsche 992 GT3 and 992 Turbo S Cabriolet (in Rubystone Red), and some other amazing and unusual cars from a shortened classic Mini, to a Unimog!|A huge thank you to Luc and the team at the Poirier Collection for the opportunity to visit, explore, and share the dream venue!|https://www.instagram.com/lucpoirier7|Thanks for watching, Tim|Chapters:|00:00 Intro|00:51 Walkaround of the Ferrari Lineup|06:34 Checking out the Other Cars|10:10 Washing Bay|11:09 Number Plates|11:35 Fun Area|13:08 Final Look Around |14:15 Wrap Up|#PoirierCollection #Supercars #Montreal||||Subscribe: http://bit.ly/Shmee150YT||Website: http://www.shmee150.com||Shop: http://shop.shmee150.com||Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/shmee150||Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/shmee150

title: Racism in Australia - Violence against aboriginal Australians | DW Documentary
description: Racism and xenophobia are a structural problem in Australia. There, racism and xenophobia are mainly directed against the indigenous population and people with Asian and Muslim roots.|Organizations that advocate for a white Australia and take openly radical right-wing positions exist and are a problem. Right-wing parties and evangelical preachers are becoming increasingly popular. This is the dark side of the popular travel destination "Down Under": racism and xenophobia. |Australia's indigenous people are speaking out, saying they feel increasingly marginalized in their own country. "I can't breathe," were the last words of David Dungay in a Sydney police cell. His is just one of 432 deaths in state custody that have occurred in Australia over the past 30 years. |More than half of all young people who end up in court accused of crimes are from indigenous families. This marginalized community is plagued by unemployment, few prospects and substance abuse. Australia's increasingly conservative society responds with repressive measures, sometimes even going as far as removing children from their families. The goal seems to be a total assimilation of the indigenous population. |#documentary #dwdocumentary #Australia #indigenouspeople|______|DW Documentary gives you knowledge beyond the headlines. title: Rafale jets collide mid-air during airshow in France; Macron govt orders probe | Watch
description: Terrifying moment of two French Rafale fighter jets mid-air collision has been caught on camera. The incident happened during the Cognac airshow- at Chateaubernard military base. Colonel Nicholas Liot, commander of the military base, said the collision that happened on Sunday was 'very rare'. The top tail of one of the two jets got severed in the collision. The aircraft managed to land safely. However, the debris of the jet fell on a house in the neighbouring village, damaging its roof. The French govt and Dassault have now ordered a probe as this is the second such accident of Rafale jets in 2022. India too, has 35 Rafale jets while one more is expected to arrive soon. Watch the mid-air horror.|#RafaleJetsCollision #MidAirScare #DassaultAviation #MacronOrdersProbe

title: Mesut Ozil Sapa Fan Indonesia Bersama Sandiaga Uno: Assalamualaikum
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS TV  Bintang sepakbola asal Jerman Mesut Ozil telah hadir di Indonesia dalam rangka produk kolaborasi merk alat olahraga Concave.||||Salah satu agendanya adalah gelar konferensi pers bersama Kementerian Pariwisata dan Ekonomi Kreatif.||||Menparekraf Sandiaga Uno hadir langsung menemani Ozil di panggung. Ozil pun sampaikan rasa semangatnya datang ke Indonesia.||||Baca Juga Momen Mesut Ozil tiba di Indonesia hingga Pamer Makan Rendang di https://www.kompas.tv/article/292401/momen-mesut-ozil-tiba-di-indonesia-hingga-pamer-makan-rendang||||"Saya ingin mengatakan, Assalamualaikum. Saya sangat bersemangat ketika tahu di Indonesia, saya punya banyak pengikut di sini," ucap Ozil.||||Ia pun mengaku bahwa ia telah bertemu beberapa dari masyarakat Indonesia dan berterima kasih atas kebaikan hatinya.||||"Saya bertemu beberapa dari kalian, dan kalian amat baik. Terima kasih."||||Ozil juga diagendakan hadir ke pabrik Concave di Indonesia, tepatnya di Cikupa, Banten.||||Mesut Ozil tiba di Indonesia sejak Selasa (24/5) malam, dan disambut sejumlah penggemarnya.||||Ozil merupakan pesepakbola asal Jerman yang kini membela klub Fenerbahce.||||Nama Ozil bersinar ketika ia sempat membela dua klub besar Eropa, Real Madrid dan Arsenal.||||Video Editor: Laurensius Galih||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/292563/mesut-ozil-sapa-fan-indonesia-bersama-sandiaga-uno-assalamualaikum
tags: mesut ozil assalamualaikum|mesut ozil indonesia|ozil assalamualaikum|ozil indonesia|ozil sandiaga uno

title: Unrest in Pak as Imran Khan's Islamabad March turns violent; PTI workers clash with cops in Lahore
description: Pakistan's ousted Prime Minister Imran Khan led a convoy of thousands of supporters towards the capital Islamabad in a show of force against the new government. Clashes between Imran supporters and police broke out in Lahore and Islamabad. In a centrepiece showdown with his rivals, Khan had called for supporters to march towards the capital and stage a sit-in until fresh elections are called. Police deployed tear gas against hundreds of Khan backers attempting to remove roadblocks in Lahore and Faizabad, where PTI supporters also seized an excavator to clear the route of containers. Watch this video for more.|#Pakistan #Lahore #AzadiMarch #ImranKhan #ShehbazSharif #Pak #Islamabad #Elections #PTI #PPP #Imran #Protest

title: Sniper Elite 5 Review
description: Reviewed by Tristan Ogilvie on Xbox Series X. Also available on Xbox, PlayStation, and PC.||||"Despite its numerous tweaks Sniper Elite 5 ultimately feels like more of an incremental upgrade than a major revolution, keeping it a half-pace ahead of Sniper Elite 4 rather than taking a big goose-step forward for the series. With a more manoeuvrable main star, modifiable weapons, enhanced co-op, and Axis Invasion allowing the hunter to become the hunted, Sniper Elite 5 is still a satisfying and spectacularly gross way to shoot Nazis in their nether regions -- but it feels like the series needs to start aiming its sights a little higher and find ways to avoid repeating the same handful of objectives so often."

title: Manoj Sinha Meets Cricketer Umran Malik In Jammu, Promises Support
description: Jammu and Kashmir Lieutenant Governor Manoj Sinha on Tuesday evening met pace sensation Umran Malik here and said the administration will take care of his training and other facilities. Malik, who received his maiden call-up for the national team for the upcoming five-match T20 International home series against South Africa starting June 9, reached his Jammu residence on Monday after taking part in the Indian Premier League (IPL). The whole country is proud (of Umran). The government will take care of his training and other facilities," Sinha told reporters after meeting Malik. title: Q & A with Sundar and Leela | #AnteSundaraniki | Nani | Nazriya Fahadh | Vivek Sagar | Vivek Athreya

title: UK evacuation from Afghanistan judged 'a disaster' - BBC Newsnight
description: A report by the UK foreign affairs select committee has laid bare serious failings in the government's evacuation of Afghans from Kabul in August 2021   Please subscribe HERE http://bit.ly/1rbfUog|The withdrawal of NATO forces from Afghanistan last year unfolded in chaos as the Taliban seized back power. |An inquiry has found 'the total absence of a plan' for evacuating Britons and Afghans who had worked with British forces. |It also found 'systemic failures in intelligence, diplomacy, planning and preparation' on behalf of the government.|Many of these Afghans are now left behind to face reprisals as #Newsnight's UK Editor Sima Kotecha discovers: |#Newsnight #BBCNews |Newsnight is the BBC's flagship news and current affairs TV programme - with analysis, debate, exclusives, and robust interviews. | |Website: https://www.bbc.co.uk/newsnight|Twitter: https://twitter.com/BBCNewsnight|Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/bbcnewsnight

title: Ozil Jawab Kemungkinan Main di Indonesia, Sebut Akan Pilih Bali United
description: JAKARTA, KOMPAS TV  Bintang sepakbola asal Jerman Mesut Ozil menyebut tak menutup kemungkinan untuk bermain di Indonesia.||||Hal tersebut ia ungkapkan saat menjawab pertanyaan wartawan soal kemungkinan berkarier di Indonesia.||||Ia mengatakan kini dirinya terikat kontrak dengan klub Turki, Fenerbahce. Namun ia akan memilih sebuah klub jika diberi kesempatan main di Indonesia.||||Baca Juga Mesut Ozil Sapa Fan Indonesia Bersama Sandiaga Uno: Assalamualaikum di https://www.kompas.tv/article/292563/mesut-ozil-sapa-fan-indonesia-bersama-sandiaga-uno-assalamualaikum||||"Saya masih dalam kontrak di Turki, bersama Fenerbahce. Saya senang berada di sana," ucap Ozil.||||"Jika saya berkesempatan untuk bermain di Indonesia, saya memilih Bali United," lanjutnya.||||Bintang sepakbola asal Jerman Mesut Ozil telah hadir di Indonesia dalam rangka produk kolaborasi merk alat olahraga Concave.||||Salah satu agendanya adalah gelar konferensi pers bersama Kementerian Pariwisata dan Ekonomi Kreatif.||||Menparekraf Sandiaga Uno hadir langsung menemani Ozil di panggung. Ozil pun sampaikan rasa semangatnya datang ke Indonesia.||||"Saya ingin mengatakan, Assalamualaikum. Saya sangat bersemangat ketika tahu di Indonesia, saya punya banyak pengikut di sini," ucap Ozil.||||Ia pun mengaku bahwa ia telah bertemu beberapa dari masyarakat Indonesia dan berterima kasih atas kebaikan hatinya.||||"Saya bertemu beberapa dari kalian, dan kalian amat baik. Terima kasih."||||Video Editor: Laurensius Galih||||Artikel ini bisa dilihat di :  https://www.kompas.tv/article/292594/ozil-jawab-kemungkinan-main-di-indonesia-sebut-akan-pilih-bali-united
